Apostle Johnson Suleman of Omega Fire Ministries has reacted as Arsenal player, Bukayo Saka contemplates which country to play for between England and Nigeria. The Arsenal’s left-back had said he was yet to decide on representing Nigeria or England in international football. Saka was born to Nigerian parents and has represented the youth teams of the Three Lions. However, the 18-year-old is yet to feature for the English senior side, which makes him still eligible for the Super Eagles. “I am always thinking about it but I haven’t made a decision yet,” Saka told BBC Sport. “No-one has been in touch but when I make a decision you will find out.” However, Apostle Suleman in a tweet said: “Our own Arsenal left~back Bukayo saka says he is contemplating playing for Nigeria. “Even when no one from here has contacted him to consider such, what do you think?” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.